As of the 2013 season, Fox NFL games will be seen on Fox's new [[owned and operated station]], [[WJZY]].<ref name="Television" /> -->

==Rivalries==
{{Main|Buccaneers–Panthers rivalry|Falcons–Panthers rivalry}}

The Panthers have developed a number of rivalries during their time in the NFL, including heated ones with the three fellow members of the NFC South (the Atlanta Falcons, Tampa Bay Buccaneers, and New Orleans Saints).<ref name="Sorensen: Falcons vs. Panthers is no rivalry">{{cite web|url=http://www.charlotteobserver.com/2008/09/28/218960/sorensen-falcons-vs-panthers-is.html|title=Sorensen: Falcons vs. Panthers is no rivalry|last=Sorenson|first=Tom|date=September 28, 2008|work=The Charlotte Observer|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Saints, Panthers rivalry deepening after New Orleans' 30-27 win ">{{cite web|url=http://www.wwltv.com/sports/black-and-gold/Saints-Panthers-rivalry-deepening-after-New-Orleans-30-27-win-131475403.html|title=Saints, Panthers rivalry deepening after New Orleans' 30–27 win |date=October 21, 2011|publisher=[[WWL-TV|WWLTV.com]]|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref> The team's fiercest rivals are the Falcons<ref name="Panthers score some points for Rivera">{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/nflnation/post/_/id/68147/panthers-score-some-points-for-rivera|title=Panthers score some points for Rivera|last=Yasinskas|first=Pat|date=December 9, 2012|publisher=ESPN.com|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref> and Buccaneers.<ref name="Sorensen: Falcons vs. Panthers is no rivalry" /> The Falcons are a natural geographic rival for the Panthers, as Atlanta is only 230 miles (370 kilometers) south on [[I-85 Corridor|I-85]].<ref name="Sorensen: Falcons vs. Panthers is no rivalry" /> The Panthers' rivalry with Tampa Bay is perhaps the most heated rivalry in the NFC South.<ref name="NFC South's most intense rivalry: Panthers vs. Bucs" /> The rivalry originated in 2003 and started with verbal bouts between players on the two teams. It escalated further when the Panthers went to Tampa Bay and beat them in what ESPN.com writer Pat Yasinskas described as "one of the most physical contests in recent memory". The rivalry has resulted in a number of severe injuries for players on both teams, some of which have been caused by foul play.<ref name="NFC South's most intense rivalry: Panthers vs. Bucs">{{cite web|url=http://espn.go.com/blog/nfcsouth/post/_/id/292/nfc-south-s-most-intense-rivalry-panthers-vs-bucs|title=NFC South's most intense rivalry: Panthers vs. Bucs|last=Yasinskas|first=Pat|date=September 11, 2008|publisher=ESPN.com|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Carolina Panthers cornerback Dante Wesley suspended for hit on Tampa Bay Buccaneers returner Clifton Smith" /> One of these plays, an illegal hit on Tampa Bay punt returner [[Clifton Smith (return specialist)|Clifton Smith]], sparked a brief melee between the two teams.<ref name="Carolina Panthers cornerback Dante Wesley suspended for hit on Tampa Bay Buccaneers returner Clifton Smith">{{cite web|url=http://www.tampabay.com/sports/football/bucs/carolina-panthers-cornerback-dante-wesley-suspended-for-hit-on-tampa-bay/1045286|title=Carolina Panthers cornerback Dante Wesley suspended for hit on Tampa Bay Buccaneers returner Clifton Smith|last=Holder|first=Stephen F.|date=October 19, 2009|work=[[Tampa Bay Times]]|accessdate=March 4, 2013}}</ref>

Outside the division, the Panthers have several other rivals. During their time in the NFC West, the Panthers began developing a rivalry with the San Francisco 49ers. However, this rivalry faded after the NFL moved the Panthers out of the NFC West.<ref name="My Panthers-49ers prediction">{{cite web|url=http://scottfowlerobs.blogspot.com/2010/10/my-panthers-49ers-prediction.html|title=My Panthers-49ers prediction|last=Fowler|first=Scott|date=October 22, 2010|publisher=Scott Says. [[The Charlotte Observer]]|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref> The Panthers maintain rivalries with the Arizona Cardinals and Dallas Cowboys, both of whom the Panthers play frequently.<ref name="Cards, Panthers resume rivalry">{{cite web|url=http://www.azcentral.com/sports/cardinals/articles/2009/10/31/20091031spt-cardscarolinaadv.html|title=Cards, Panthers resume rivalry|last=Somers|first=Kent|date=October 31, 2009|work=[[The Arizona Republic]]|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref><ref name="Cowboys-Panthers Rivalry Has Seen Interesting Twists & Turns ">{{cite web|url=http://www.dallascowboys.com/news/article-NickEatman/Cowboys-Panthers-Rivalry-Has-Seen-Interesting-Twists--Turns-/13954fba-f5cb-4aef-ac77-84e4ee2a3bde|title=Cowboys-Panthers Rivalry Has Seen Interesting Twists & Turns |last=Eatman|first=Nick|date=October 19, 2012|publisher=Dallas Cowboys|accessdate=January 22, 2013}}</ref>

